text:
[THREAD] 👇

SpaceX is preparing for its historic first human mission launch this afternoon. 

Liftoff is scheduled for 3:22 p.m. ET, though poor weather and other factors could delay the mission once again. 

https://t.co/2PjTqVwxIS

name: businessinsider
text:
SpaceX attempted a Wednesday launch, going so far as to fuel the rocket with two astronauts inside the spaceship. Problematic clouds and the threat of lightning forced them to scrub the attempt.

Here's why they couldn't just wait for the clouds to clear.
https://t.co/jyYzdGdAWA

name: businessinsider
text:
SpaceX, NASA, Neil deGrasse Tyson, National Geographic and ABC News, and others will be broadcasting live video coverage of the mission, most of which you can watch online here:

https://t.co/2PjTqVwxIS

name: businessinsider
text:
The new Crew Dragon spaceship will be piloted by NASA astronauts Bob Behnken and Doug Hurley during the test flight.

Both are military test pilots, engineers, members of the same NASA astronaut class, and have flown on two space-shuttle missions.

https://t.co/rFn79LsL69

name: businessinsider
text:
NASA is broadcasting live audio from the mission, called Demo-2.

You'll be able to hear what astronauts Bob Behnken and Doug Hurley say aboard the SpaceX spacecraft as the rocket launches from Cape Canaveral, Florida. 

You can find the stream here:
https://t.co/1N7YXIV0eY
